1
00:00:00,125 --> 00:00:02,335
By the way,

2
00:00:02,360 --> 00:00:03,795
do you remember me?

3
00:00:03,820 --> 00:00:05,200
It's just...

4
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:07,680
Mindy!

5
00:00:07,705 --> 00:00:09,317
- Serves them right!
- Mindy!

6
00:00:09,544 --> 00:00:10,544
Get out!

7
00:00:11,844 --> 00:00:15,108
Just that I don't know
if I can forgive him.

8
00:00:15,133 --> 00:00:16,475
Excuse me.

9
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:18,160
Did you write this with your foot?

10
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:20,040
Jira.

11
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:23,320
Are you really not
going to forgive me?

12
00:00:25,076 --> 00:00:28,400
Being the same sex
is unnatural enough.

13
00:00:29,293 --> 00:00:31,336
Don't make it any more perverted.

14
00:00:32,393 --> 00:00:34,113
You don't understand
anything at all.

15
00:00:36,560 --> 00:00:39,815
You came to apologize
for your own peace of mind.

16
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:41,575
And I forgive you.

17
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:46,320
For my own peace of mind
in my final years too.

18
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:09,520
Hmm?

19
00:01:10,778 --> 00:01:11,800
Hmm?

20
00:01:22,667 --> 00:01:23,667
Hmm.

21
00:02:05,342 --> 00:02:06,400
Jee!

22
00:02:06,425 --> 00:02:08,255
Hey, Jee!

23
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:10,960
What happened?

24
00:02:15,661 --> 00:02:16,661
I saw...

25
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:19,480
In the mirror!

26
00:02:20,121 --> 00:02:21,841
- What?
- In the mirror!

27
00:02:23,205 --> 00:02:26,120
An old man ghost!

28
00:02:27,533 --> 00:02:31,520
Bald, hollow eyes, no teeth at all.

29
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:33,680
It came out to haunt me.

30
00:02:35,852 --> 00:02:36,858
Jee...

31
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:39,905
There's nothing there.

32
00:02:39,930 --> 00:02:43,234
You might be sleepy.

33
00:02:43,935 --> 00:02:45,983
- And half-asleep.
- So scary!

34
00:02:46,008 --> 00:02:48,400
The light isn't very bright either.

35
00:02:49,998 --> 00:02:51,005
What?

36
00:02:51,956 --> 00:02:55,040
There's nothing there.

37
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:57,286
There, there. Nothing scary.

38
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,421
It's nothing.

39
00:03:01,530 --> 00:03:02,530
So scary.

40
00:03:04,576 --> 00:03:05,840
It was really scary.

41
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:09,360
"Jee is so worried
he's hallucinating."

42
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:12,850
"He definitely won't
be able to sleep tonight."

43
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,480
Such a simple thing,

44
00:03:57,960 --> 00:04:00,560
like cleaning up
your own hair scraps.

45
00:04:01,222 --> 00:04:03,440
Do I really have to do it for you?

46
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,120
Someone's going
to lose sleep tonight.

47
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:10,720
Jee.

48
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:13,240
Jee.

49
00:04:13,490 --> 00:04:15,040
- Hmm...
- What?

50
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:16,800
Hmm?

51
00:04:18,583 --> 00:04:19,583
Hmm?

52
00:04:20,328 --> 00:04:21,480
Take a look for me.

53
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:24,021
Why aren't you asleep yet?

54
00:04:24,613 --> 00:04:25,820
What are you doing?

55
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,240
Check this for me.

56
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,173
Am I bald yet?

57
00:04:30,549 --> 00:04:31,560
Is it ugly?

58
00:04:41,909 --> 00:04:42,909
Hmm?

59
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,000
- Hmm?
- Um.

60
00:04:46,631 --> 00:04:47,631
Not yet.

61
00:04:48,984 --> 00:04:51,764
I don't see any bald spots.
It's just thinning a little bit.

62
00:04:51,789 --> 00:04:52,875
Huh?

63
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:57,200
Thinning hair is natural, Jee.

64
00:04:58,280 --> 00:04:59,280
Don't worry about it.

65
00:05:02,705 --> 00:05:03,705
Am I...

66
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:06,330
going...

67
00:05:06,355 --> 00:05:07,408
bald?

68
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:09,440
Bald.

69
00:05:10,668 --> 00:05:11,668
Bald?

70
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:30,360
- Jee.
- Hmm.

71
00:05:31,086 --> 00:05:32,086
Get some sleep.

72
00:05:32,446 --> 00:05:34,360
Worrying too much
makes you age faster.

73
00:05:37,883 --> 00:05:40,480
Age faster means going bald faster!

74
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,120
No...

75
00:05:45,410 --> 00:05:47,058
What do you mean age faster?

76
00:05:47,390 --> 00:05:49,082
You're only 55.

77
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:51,767
You still look young and handsome,

78
00:05:51,791 --> 00:05:54,213
like you're only in your early 30s.

79
00:06:07,069 --> 00:06:08,840
Don't worry about it..

80
00:06:21,351 --> 00:06:24,760
"Liver spots...
just like an old man."

81
00:06:25,608 --> 00:06:29,800
"His skin is
starting to show signs."

82
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:44,760
"Turns out, tonight,
neither Jee nor I..."

83
00:06:45,663 --> 00:06:46,800
"can sleep."

84
00:06:55,368 --> 00:06:56,635
Please, have a seat.

85
00:06:56,660 --> 00:07:00,411
Our Deputy Managing Director
is stuck in another meeting.

86
00:07:00,436 --> 00:07:02,080
She might be a little late.

87
00:07:02,527 --> 00:07:04,200
Yes, please.

88
00:07:07,035 --> 00:07:09,000
Hello everyone.

89
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,880
- Hello.
- Have you been waiting long?

90
00:07:11,399 --> 00:07:12,520
Thank you.

91
00:07:12,545 --> 00:07:15,160
- Hello.
- Hello.

92
00:07:15,695 --> 00:07:19,975
Hello,
Ms. Deputy Managing Director.

93
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,540
Just call me Gift.

94
00:07:21,564 --> 00:07:23,695
We seem to be around
the same age anyway.

95
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:28,002
Hello, Ms. Gift. Nice to meet you.

96
00:07:28,027 --> 00:07:29,360
I must apologize.

97
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:33,465
At first, I thought
you were Mr. Jira's secretary.

98
00:07:33,465 --> 00:07:38,036
Oh my, age isn't an indicator
of work quality, is it?

99
00:07:38,061 --> 00:07:39,569
Look at you guys.

100
00:07:39,593 --> 00:07:42,895
The storyboard you
proposed was excellent.

101
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:44,237
I like everything about it.

102
00:07:44,261 --> 00:07:46,415
Only a small adjustment.

103
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:49,023
We'd be happy to.

104
00:07:49,048 --> 00:07:51,766
We just went to block the shots.

105
00:07:51,791 --> 00:07:53,400
And we filmed a sample too.

106
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:56,240
Would you like to
see it before adjusting?

107
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,535
Sure. How would you
like to send it to me?

108
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,670
Slack?

109
00:07:59,695 --> 00:08:02,255
Oh, I don't have that.
It looks too complicated.

110
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:05,259
It's okay. I do have it.

111
00:08:05,970 --> 00:08:07,640
In that case,
may I have your email?

112
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:08,840
So I can Direct Message you.

113
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:10,480
Certainly.

114
00:08:14,665 --> 00:08:15,880
Good location.

115
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:18,960
- Will it take long?
- Half a day, probably.

116
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:29,409
Should we go?
I want to get a Shelly figure.

117
00:08:29,434 --> 00:08:31,560
Wait a sec. Let me finish
this Duckman thing first.

118
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,541
Is it good?

119
00:08:33,566 --> 00:08:35,720
Not really.
But I like the art style.

120
00:08:38,218 --> 00:08:40,295
You like this outdated style?

121
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,440
It's detailed!

122
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,880
The line for Beam's autograph
is getting long. Let's go now.

123
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:48,160
Let's go.

124
00:08:53,508 --> 00:08:55,414
"You like this outdated style?"

125
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:57,160
Outdated style?

126
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,400
Ohn, hello.

127
00:09:04,649 --> 00:09:05,649
Hello.

128
00:09:06,165 --> 00:09:07,525
Are you here to sign autographs?

129
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:08,640
Oh, no.

130
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:13,942
Just looking around.
Quite vibrant, isn't it?

131
00:09:13,967 --> 00:09:15,537
Lots of teenagers walking around.

132
00:09:15,562 --> 00:09:17,707
They come to buy
Shelly B-Bell figures.

133
00:09:18,669 --> 00:09:19,789
Shelly B-Bell?

134
00:09:20,345 --> 00:09:23,295
A character from a comic
by an artist named Beam.

135
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,573
He's really popular right now.

136
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:27,615
Only 28 years old.

137
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:31,000
He's as famous as you were
way back when you wrote Kittima.

138
00:09:34,028 --> 00:09:35,083
Mmm.

139
00:09:35,108 --> 00:09:36,128
Well...

140
00:09:37,793 --> 00:09:40,423
Has anyone picked up
the Duckman pilot?

141
00:09:41,058 --> 00:09:44,511
Some people asked about the e-book.

142
00:09:44,536 --> 00:09:46,834
But I don't know
if they scanned to read it.

143
00:09:46,859 --> 00:09:48,480
We'll have to see
after the event ends.

144
00:09:49,476 --> 00:09:51,280
Oh, I see.

145
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:57,260
Oh, someone asked
if the author of Duckman

146
00:09:57,285 --> 00:09:59,333
is the same person
who writes the blog

147
00:09:59,358 --> 00:10:01,200
"Diary of a Comic Artist Hub"?

148
00:10:01,974 --> 00:10:04,280
I don't know.
I've never heard of it.

149
00:10:04,305 --> 00:10:06,127
I didn't think so either.

150
00:10:06,152 --> 00:10:08,480
You don't look very tech-savvy.

151
00:10:11,356 --> 00:10:13,880
I'm gonna go walk around a bit.

152
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,800
- Sure. Bye.
- Bye.

153
00:10:36,017 --> 00:10:37,880
Tighten your abs. Okay.

154
00:10:37,905 --> 00:10:39,446
Good... Okay.

155
00:10:39,471 --> 00:10:41,280
Do I need to hold it that long?

156
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:42,920
About three seconds.

157
00:11:00,613 --> 00:11:01,706
Hey, A.

158
00:11:02,808 --> 00:11:04,440
Do I have to lift that too?

159
00:11:05,207 --> 00:11:06,327
I don't think I can.

160
00:11:06,736 --> 00:11:10,775
Come on, you just
started weight training.

161
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:15,113
You should take it easy.
Master the basics first.

162
00:11:15,138 --> 00:11:18,120
At my condo, I swim often.

163
00:11:18,862 --> 00:11:20,012
Is that not enough?

164
00:11:20,037 --> 00:11:24,400
Swimming is the best.

165
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:29,255
A low-impact exercise for joints.

166
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,840
Very suitable for the elderly.

167
00:11:35,445 --> 00:11:37,030
I'm so full.

168
00:11:37,054 --> 00:11:39,175
I shouldn't have eaten that much.

169
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,628
Hey, can you help me
buy a lotion? I'm too shy.

170
00:11:41,653 --> 00:11:42,678
Shy about what?

171
00:11:42,703 --> 00:11:45,543
It's good that you're
taking care of your skin early on.

172
00:11:45,568 --> 00:11:47,880
Are you afraid people will
tease you for being LGBTQ+?

173
00:11:47,904 --> 00:11:51,975
No, I'm shy because I don't know
anything about lotions at all.

174
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,006
That's fine.

175
00:11:53,031 --> 00:11:55,360
It's good that you're
thinking about using lotion now.

176
00:11:55,385 --> 00:11:56,498
When you get old...

177
00:11:56,523 --> 00:12:00,175
your natural oils and sebaceous
glands will produce less oil

178
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:02,440
making your skin dehydrated.

179
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:04,333
It will become flaky and dry.

180
00:12:04,357 --> 00:12:05,606
Not pretty at all.

181
00:12:06,479 --> 00:12:08,960
Come on, looking good
isn't all that important

182
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:11,844
as long as you don't get
skin cancer when you're old.

183
00:12:11,869 --> 00:12:13,880
How about you guys
help me pick a lotion,

184
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:16,055
and I'll help with your workout?

185
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:18,410
Working out now and you'll
be strong when you're old.

186
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:20,680
Deal. Let's go.

187
00:12:24,193 --> 00:12:27,720
But you guys are worried
about losing muscle mass

188
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:30,160
as you're getting
older and older, right?

189
00:12:31,390 --> 00:12:32,440
Hmm.

190
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:37,710
Weight training can help build
fast-twitch muscle fibers the best.

191
00:12:38,193 --> 00:12:40,896
Otherwise, when you get old,

192
00:12:40,928 --> 00:12:44,596
you'll become thin and frail,
blown away by the wind.

193
00:12:45,880 --> 00:12:47,124
Being thin is good.

194
00:12:47,148 --> 00:12:49,895
For once in my life,
I'd love to be slim and slender.

195
00:12:49,920 --> 00:12:51,863
But people with low muscle mass,

196
00:12:51,887 --> 00:12:53,168
when they get old,

197
00:12:53,193 --> 00:12:56,296
falling hurts more than
people with high muscle mass.

198
00:12:57,017 --> 00:12:58,023
Jeez.

199
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:01,400
Are you done yet? Shall we go?

200
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:03,640
I'm hungry.

201
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:06,225
Want to join us, Ohn?

202
00:13:06,249 --> 00:13:07,713
Some delicious pickled crab?

203
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:10,360
Pickled crab?

204
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:13,680
Clean eating, remember?

205
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:17,055
Be patient. Wait for cheat day.

206
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:19,119
Oh, come on... Jee!

207
00:13:19,144 --> 00:13:20,240
Mmm-hmm.

208
00:13:22,452 --> 00:13:27,200
Well, they both need to start
taking better care of themselves.

209
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:28,640
Before they get too old.

210
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,600
In that case, let's move cheat day?

211
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:35,286
Cheat today,
then make it up on another day.

212
00:13:35,311 --> 00:13:36,391
Okay?

213
00:13:36,415 --> 00:13:39,000
Move cheat day.
Eat today, make up for it later.

214
00:13:39,025 --> 00:13:41,440
Cheat day today, okay?

215
00:13:41,472 --> 00:13:44,760
Please?

216
00:13:44,785 --> 00:13:46,011
Think about pickled crab.

217
00:13:46,944 --> 00:13:47,955
Please?

218
00:13:47,980 --> 00:13:48,986
Please...

219
00:13:49,155 --> 00:13:50,155
Fine.

220
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:53,600
- Okay, see you then.
- You're the cutest!

221
00:13:54,405 --> 00:13:56,720
You guys rode
a motorcycle here, right?

222
00:14:02,710 --> 00:14:05,440
Isn't that a motorcycle bandana?

223
00:14:13,618 --> 00:14:17,072
Jee, it's okay.
Don't worry about it.

224
00:14:17,097 --> 00:14:19,045
You still look so good.

225
00:14:19,070 --> 00:14:20,923
Still handsome as ever.

226
00:14:21,463 --> 00:14:23,323
- Always.
- Hmm...

227
00:14:23,348 --> 00:14:25,278
- Believe me.
- Hmm...

228
00:14:26,175 --> 00:14:27,175
Mmm.

229
00:14:55,920 --> 00:14:57,853
You, old man.

230
00:14:58,653 --> 00:15:00,280
Don't be too stressed.

231
00:15:00,960 --> 00:15:04,486
The more you stress,
the more your hair will fall out.

232
00:15:04,511 --> 00:15:06,268
- Huh?
- Hmm.

233
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:10,840
Easy for you to say.
You haven't lost much hair.

234
00:15:13,233 --> 00:15:15,612
My job involves
meeting lots of people.

235
00:15:15,637 --> 00:15:20,907
Just being older than
my boss is stressful enough.

236
00:15:20,932 --> 00:15:22,115
Now, look at me.

237
00:15:22,139 --> 00:15:24,558
I look untrustworthy,
unreliable like this.

238
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:28,520
Trust isn't about...

239
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:33,240
whether you have hair or not.

240
00:15:33,994 --> 00:15:36,320
But I don't feel good about myself.

241
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,593
Of course.
You still have thick hair.

242
00:15:39,617 --> 00:15:41,975
A nice and thick set of hair.

243
00:15:46,559 --> 00:15:49,000
And if my hair falls out in patches

244
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,367
Here and there...

245
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:54,000
It won't look good, right?

246
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:57,840
And you will leave me.

247
00:15:59,164 --> 00:16:00,880
How will I survive?

248
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:02,760
Hey! Wait...

249
00:16:03,727 --> 00:16:05,200
That's my line.

250
00:16:05,969 --> 00:16:09,520
The one who should be
afraid of being dumped is me.

251
00:16:12,320 --> 00:16:13,680
Sometimes I do...

252
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:16,520
fear getting dumped.

253
00:16:18,204 --> 00:16:21,160
Aww...

254
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,440
I won't leave you.

255
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:32,185
Even if you...

256
00:16:33,904 --> 00:16:35,513
go bald in patches.

257
00:16:36,687 --> 00:16:38,355
Or totally bald.

258
00:16:38,380 --> 00:16:41,120
As bald as an egg,
no hair in sight.

259
00:16:41,145 --> 00:16:43,200
Shiny enough
to see your reflection...

260
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,575
Enough! That's quite enough.

261
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:48,880
That was just straight-up bullying.

262
00:16:49,478 --> 00:16:50,918
I'm really going to cry.

263
00:16:50,943 --> 00:16:53,207
I was just teasing you.

264
00:16:54,505 --> 00:16:55,705
Please don't cry.

265
00:16:56,196 --> 00:16:59,246
I do love you.

266
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:00,840
Shiny enough for you?

267
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:02,880
- Do you still love me?
- Hmm...

268
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:05,113
- Handsome enough for you?
- No matter what, I love you.

269
00:17:05,649 --> 00:17:06,828
A big kiss for you.

270
00:17:06,853 --> 00:17:07,853
This side too.

271
00:17:08,697 --> 00:17:09,703
Bleh!

272
00:17:35,530 --> 00:17:36,760
Jee.

273
00:17:37,171 --> 00:17:38,171
What are you doing?

274
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:42,200
Waiting to wash my hair.

275
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:46,117
- Waiting to wash your hair?
- Mmm-hmm.

276
00:17:46,645 --> 00:17:47,645
Wait.

277
00:17:48,367 --> 00:17:51,600
Why are you doing
a hair treatment this late?

278
00:17:51,625 --> 00:17:53,763
I found a recipe

279
00:17:54,591 --> 00:17:57,240
for hair loss on the internet.
So I'm trying it out.

280
00:17:57,240 --> 00:18:00,040
All you need is
just olive oil and honey.

281
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:01,696
Leave it on for 15 minutes.

282
00:18:01,721 --> 00:18:05,111
But I was afraid it wouldn't work,
so I left it on for an hour.

283
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:07,840
- Oh Jee...
- Wait, wait.

284
00:18:07,865 --> 00:18:11,080
There's another recipe.

285
00:18:11,080 --> 00:18:12,338
Using salt and warm water.

286
00:18:12,362 --> 00:18:13,681
Only five minutes.

287
00:18:13,705 --> 00:18:16,176
I was thinking that if this one
didn't work, I'd try that one.

288
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:18,363
Oh, and I found
a hair thickening spray.

289
00:18:18,387 --> 00:18:20,387
I already ordered one to try.

290
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:24,102
- Jee.
- Hmm?

291
00:18:24,127 --> 00:18:25,807
You should go wash your hair.

292
00:18:26,633 --> 00:18:29,573
Leaving it on too long
might not be good.

293
00:18:29,598 --> 00:18:30,598
What?

294
00:18:31,025 --> 00:18:32,581
- Really?
- Hmm.

295
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:34,840
- Go rinse it.
- Okay.

296
00:18:35,690 --> 00:18:36,920
Rinse it off.

297
00:18:40,117 --> 00:18:41,643
"I might not
be able to sleep tonight"

298
00:18:42,038 --> 00:18:45,360
"if my love is worried
about his hair like this."

299
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:49,240
"But it's okay."

300
00:18:50,004 --> 00:18:51,853
"Tomorrow is a holiday."

301
00:19:06,367 --> 00:19:07,367
Jee.

302
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:14,880
Who is it?

303
00:19:15,353 --> 00:19:18,160
I don't know. You, go check.

304
00:19:20,225 --> 00:19:21,240
Mmm-mmm.

305
00:19:22,326 --> 00:19:24,013
- Play an old person.
- Play an old person.

306
00:19:26,050 --> 00:19:29,615
I know asking you both now
might not be a good timing.

307
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:31,880
But I really don't know
who else to turn to.

308
00:19:35,593 --> 00:19:36,739
I can't

309
00:19:36,764 --> 00:19:38,506
This afternoon I'm taking care of

310
00:19:38,530 --> 00:19:40,530
the Assistant Minister
for an inspection.

311
00:19:41,777 --> 00:19:44,203
I'm late now! Take care of him.

312
00:19:44,228 --> 00:19:47,911
Wait, Aom!

313
00:19:47,936 --> 00:19:48,956
- Wait, Aom!
- Uncle Ohn.

314
00:19:48,981 --> 00:19:50,801
- I've got to go.
- Aom!

315
00:19:55,257 --> 00:19:56,257
Oh my.

316
00:19:57,415 --> 00:19:58,840
Those puppy eyes again.

317
00:20:00,339 --> 00:20:05,721
Ikkyu, there're old people
around you, like Grandma.

318
00:20:05,746 --> 00:20:07,320
Why don't you film her?

319
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:11,415
I tried, but it didn't work.

320
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:13,460
She said a few words
and forgot the rest.

321
00:20:13,484 --> 00:20:14,850
We had to keep reshooting.

322
00:20:17,171 --> 00:20:18,200
Action!

323
00:20:19,003 --> 00:20:21,224
In this hot weather,

324
00:20:21,249 --> 00:20:24,680
if I could have a glass of
chrysanthemum tea or longan tea,

325
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:27,236
it would be so refreshing.

326
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:29,080
Cut!

327
00:20:29,673 --> 00:20:30,895
Why?

328
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:32,199
Plain water, Grandma.

329
00:20:32,223 --> 00:20:34,161
Where did you get
chrysanthemum or longan from?

330
00:20:34,185 --> 00:20:36,596
Well, I saw them in that fridge.

331
00:20:37,154 --> 00:20:38,826
No, you have to follow the script.

332
00:20:38,850 --> 00:20:40,121
Follow the script?

333
00:20:40,146 --> 00:20:42,840
You have to say,
In this hot weather...

334
00:20:42,840 --> 00:20:44,183
In this hot weather...

335
00:20:44,208 --> 00:20:46,875
- If I could have some cold water
- If I could have some cold water

336
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:48,520
- it would be nice.
- it would be nice.

337
00:20:48,682 --> 00:20:50,400
- Mmm.
- One more time.

338
00:20:52,507 --> 00:20:53,507
Okay.

339
00:20:55,257 --> 00:20:56,257
Action!

340
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:58,046
In this hot weather,

341
00:20:58,071 --> 00:20:59,877
if I could have a glass of
cold chrysanthemum,

342
00:20:59,902 --> 00:21:01,058
it would be nice.

343
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:04,080
Did I say it wrong?

344
00:21:05,965 --> 00:21:07,120
Cold water, Grandma.

345
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:09,393
Sorry, dear. Cold water, okay?

346
00:21:09,418 --> 00:21:11,440
- Not chrysanthemum.
- Not chrysanthemum.

347
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:12,880
Okay, okay.

348
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:15,920
Action!

349
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:18,760
In this hot weather,
not chrysanthemum,

350
00:21:18,760 --> 00:21:21,575
A glass of cold water is nice.

351
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:23,360
Did I get it right?

352
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:28,489
She couldn't remember her lines.

353
00:21:28,513 --> 00:21:30,016
She kept forgetting.

354
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:31,596
I wonder if she has Alzheimer's.

355
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:33,520
Alzheimer's?

356
00:21:34,269 --> 00:21:35,440
I don't think so.

357
00:21:36,167 --> 00:21:37,753
She might just be nervous.

358
00:21:37,753 --> 00:21:40,440
So she's getting
her lines mixed up.

359
00:21:41,142 --> 00:21:42,480
I hope so.

360
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:45,360
She often forgets to turn off
the lights and the faucet.

361
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:48,680
I have to keep checking,
or Mom will scold her.

362
00:21:49,287 --> 00:21:52,600
Your sister is
looking after her quite well.

363
00:21:53,201 --> 00:21:55,720
If it's Alzheimer's,
she would know.

364
00:21:56,337 --> 00:22:00,200
You two will be
the actors and crew, right?

365
00:22:02,560 --> 00:22:04,120
Crew too?

366
00:22:10,791 --> 00:22:12,040
Making those eyes again.

367
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:14,840
We can't refuse, can we?

368
00:22:28,890 --> 00:22:29,960
Hmm...

369
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:34,457
I think this one is okay.

370
00:22:35,121 --> 00:22:36,121
Hmm?

371
00:22:37,855 --> 00:22:38,921
Oh, who's that?

372
00:22:39,395 --> 00:22:40,640
I'll get it.

373
00:22:40,640 --> 00:22:42,160
Thank you.

374
00:22:48,818 --> 00:22:49,938
Oh!

375
00:22:51,157 --> 00:22:52,200
Hello.

376
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:53,880
Who is it, sweetie?

377
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:55,800
Sweetie?

378
00:22:58,457 --> 00:22:59,457
Mom.

379
00:23:10,018 --> 00:23:12,058
Well, her favorite son wasn't free.

380
00:23:12,083 --> 00:23:13,960
So I had to take her
to see the doctor myself.

381
00:23:14,583 --> 00:23:16,280
What's wrong, Mom?

382
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:19,323
Nothing at all. I'm perfectly fine.

383
00:23:19,831 --> 00:23:22,486
- Just an annual check-up.
- Hmm.

384
00:23:22,518 --> 00:23:27,600
She's fit as a fiddle,
and very healthy for her age.

385
00:23:27,625 --> 00:23:29,120
That's good.

386
00:23:29,445 --> 00:23:31,600
At first, Mom wanted me
to take her to see her friend,

387
00:23:31,624 --> 00:23:32,685
Auntie Pannee.

388
00:23:33,727 --> 00:23:35,560
But...

389
00:23:36,512 --> 00:23:37,923
What happened to Auntie Pannee?

390
00:23:39,527 --> 00:23:41,210
It's not a good timing for her.

391
00:23:41,234 --> 00:23:43,056
She's going out.

392
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:44,134
Mmm-hmm.

393
00:23:44,159 --> 00:23:45,484
She's getting a divorce.

394
00:23:45,509 --> 00:23:46,509
What?

395
00:23:46,931 --> 00:23:48,080
Why?

396
00:23:50,040 --> 00:23:51,576
She said...

397
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:53,600
she's getting married again.

398
00:23:54,904 --> 00:23:56,360
to...

399
00:23:57,727 --> 00:23:58,760
a woman.

400
00:24:01,287 --> 00:24:02,920
Oh...

401
00:24:02,944 --> 00:24:03,944
Hmm.

402
00:24:05,945 --> 00:24:08,290
She said they've loved
each other for a very long time.

403
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:10,160
But back then,

404
00:24:11,300 --> 00:24:14,894
if two women lived
together as a couple...

405
00:24:14,919 --> 00:24:16,000
well...

406
00:24:19,010 --> 00:24:22,720
it was something
difficult for society to accept.

407
00:24:23,899 --> 00:24:24,905
Hmm.

408
00:24:25,360 --> 00:24:27,211
She also said that

409
00:24:27,235 --> 00:24:31,630
since there is
a marriage equality law now...

410
00:24:31,655 --> 00:24:32,738
Mmm-hmm.

411
00:24:32,763 --> 00:24:36,582
she has fulfilled
her duties as a daughter...

412
00:24:37,560 --> 00:24:38,690
a wife...

413
00:24:39,245 --> 00:24:41,080
and a mother completely,

414
00:24:42,527 --> 00:24:44,399
before she dies, she wants to...

415
00:24:45,899 --> 00:24:48,137
spend her life with
the person she truly loves.

416
00:24:48,162 --> 00:24:49,255
Hmm.

417
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:52,840
She wants to
follow her heart for once.

418
00:25:01,555 --> 00:25:03,216
We've been friends for so long.

419
00:25:04,360 --> 00:25:07,640
Why didn't she
tell me that she was...

420
00:25:10,328 --> 00:25:13,480
The reason she didn't tell you...

421
00:25:15,560 --> 00:25:17,020
is because she loves you very much.

422
00:25:19,286 --> 00:25:21,663
She probably didn't want
you to be disgusted by her.

423
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:25,534
She was probably afraid

424
00:25:25,558 --> 00:25:28,240
that you wouldn't want
to be her friend anymore.

425
00:25:32,373 --> 00:25:34,390
I'm not that kind of person.

426
00:25:35,480 --> 00:25:37,896
- Beverages for everyone.
- Ahh...

427
00:25:38,419 --> 00:25:40,951
- Green tea for Mom.
- Thank you, you're so sweet.

428
00:25:40,976 --> 00:25:42,176
And here is...

429
00:25:44,304 --> 00:25:47,694
black coffee, no sugar, for you.

430
00:25:47,719 --> 00:25:50,585
Thank you. It smells great.

431
00:25:51,816 --> 00:25:53,339
Thank you.

432
00:25:55,110 --> 00:25:56,305
Come, sit.

433
00:25:58,280 --> 00:26:00,920
He's really into green tea lately.

434
00:26:02,296 --> 00:26:05,920
It has antioxidants,
helps boost the immune system,

435
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:08,413
and reduces the risk of cancer too.

436
00:26:08,438 --> 00:26:09,473
Oh.

437
00:26:09,498 --> 00:26:14,280
You sound just like
an online influencer.

438
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:18,122
He said the same thing
when he's making me drink it too.

439
00:26:18,147 --> 00:26:19,803
He's afraid I'll die of cancer.

440
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:24,840
Here is some fruit.

441
00:26:25,800 --> 00:26:27,520
- Thank you, dear.
- Oh, thank you.

442
00:26:27,808 --> 00:26:29,839
And you are...

443
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:32,440
I'm a director.

444
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:33,966
Oh.

445
00:26:33,991 --> 00:26:36,371
Would you like to be an actress?

446
00:26:36,396 --> 00:26:37,396
Hmm?

447
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:44,908
In this hot weather,

448
00:26:44,933 --> 00:26:47,201
if I could have
a glass of refreshing cold water,

449
00:26:47,226 --> 00:26:48,761
it would be nice.

450
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:51,880
Cut!

451
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:59,320
- An Oscar!
- Wow, superb!

452
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:03,280
How was it, dear? Was it okay?

453
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:07,960
It was perfect!
You didn't mess up a single word.

454
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:12,360
There were only few lines.

455
00:27:12,911 --> 00:27:15,080
If there were a lot,
I wouldn't remember.

456
00:27:17,317 --> 00:27:18,640
You're very good.

457
00:27:19,294 --> 00:27:20,520
My mom couldn't even do it.

458
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:24,960
We don't know
if she has brain problems.

459
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:32,640
Ohn is a good cook.

460
00:27:32,665 --> 00:27:35,520
No wonder Jee is
so smitten with his cooking.

461
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:43,585
Look, we already ate so much here.

462
00:27:43,610 --> 00:27:46,647
Why do you also pack
so much food to take home?

463
00:27:46,672 --> 00:27:47,780
It's good, Mom.

464
00:27:47,804 --> 00:27:50,818
So you don't have to
cook for Dad when you get home.

465
00:27:52,964 --> 00:27:55,680
It's a pity
Grandma isn't free tomorrow.

466
00:27:56,552 --> 00:27:59,952
Ikkyu, give you an inch
and you take a mile.

467
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:03,403
You've already bothered her enough.

468
00:28:03,820 --> 00:28:05,881
Don't scold him.

469
00:28:05,906 --> 00:28:08,560
It's fun to do something
like this once in a while.

470
00:28:09,201 --> 00:28:10,221
Hmm.

471
00:28:11,619 --> 00:28:14,347
Thank you for your support.

472
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:16,680
Oh, Ikkyu.

473
00:28:17,007 --> 00:28:20,287
Can we go check
the location in the afternoon?

474
00:28:20,951 --> 00:28:23,800
Let us take a nap a bit first.

475
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:26,609
No can do.

476
00:28:26,633 --> 00:28:29,599
It's hot in the afternoon.
My skin will be ruined.

477
00:28:31,581 --> 00:28:32,667
That's true...

478
00:28:32,691 --> 00:28:33,776
Isn't it?

479
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:35,800
Let me know
if there's anything else to do.

480
00:28:37,911 --> 00:28:40,729
We've been standing here for ages.
Have you pressed the button?

481
00:28:40,754 --> 00:28:42,002
Oh, I forgot.

482
00:28:42,027 --> 00:28:45,080
We'll never get home at this rate.

483
00:28:45,582 --> 00:28:46,582
Are you okay?

484
00:28:48,908 --> 00:28:49,908
Oops.

485
00:28:50,847 --> 00:28:52,647
You pressed the wrong floor again.

486
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:55,160
I thought I did.

487
00:28:55,184 --> 00:28:56,240
No, you didn't.

488
00:28:56,681 --> 00:28:57,855
Sorry. Please, come in.

489
00:28:57,880 --> 00:28:59,560
- Go on.
- Go, dear.

490
00:28:59,585 --> 00:29:00,880
- Go.
- Bye.

491
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:02,303
- Bye.
- Bye, dear.

492
00:29:02,328 --> 00:29:04,120
- Bye.
- Bye.

493
00:29:05,649 --> 00:29:06,649
Press again?

494
00:29:08,555 --> 00:29:09,569
They won't get home then.

495
00:29:13,800 --> 00:29:14,920
Is it pretty?

496
00:29:14,945 --> 00:29:15,945
Hmm...

497
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:21,280
Nidnoi, Jee's mom
remembers her lines so well.

498
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:24,720
But Ikkyu said my mom...

499
00:29:25,701 --> 00:29:28,120
she's forgetful.

500
00:29:28,682 --> 00:29:30,489
She couldn't remember her lines.

501
00:29:30,776 --> 00:29:33,640
If your mom wasn't camera shy,

502
00:29:33,665 --> 00:29:35,840
it might just be
age-related forgetfulness.

503
00:29:35,864 --> 00:29:37,776
It might not be dementia.

504
00:29:38,405 --> 00:29:40,906
Then how can we tell?

505
00:29:40,931 --> 00:29:44,520
What's the difference
between dementia symptoms

506
00:29:44,545 --> 00:29:46,612
and normal
age-related forgetfulness?

507
00:29:47,150 --> 00:29:50,243
Normal aging forgetfulness is

508
00:29:50,267 --> 00:29:52,695
complaining about
forgetting this and that,

509
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:55,895
but they can still
tell you what they forgot.

510
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:58,533
Or they might
remember important events

511
00:29:58,557 --> 00:30:00,256
but take a while to recall them.

512
00:30:00,280 --> 00:30:02,015
That's still normal.

513
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:04,440
Or maybe,
they can't think of a word,

514
00:30:04,465 --> 00:30:08,313
but they can still interact
and talk to people normally.

515
00:30:08,338 --> 00:30:11,055
This isn't too worrying yet.

516
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:13,735
But there are some indicators.

517
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:14,978
Like...

518
00:30:15,908 --> 00:30:18,240
getting lost in familiar places.

519
00:30:19,767 --> 00:30:22,840
Like going to the temple
or the market nearby

520
00:30:22,840 --> 00:30:25,513
and suddenly getting confused.

521
00:30:25,537 --> 00:30:27,800
- That's when to worry, right?
- One moment, please.

522
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:52,860
- I'm back.
- Yes.

523
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:56,813
Where were we?
Yes, that's about right.

524
00:30:56,838 --> 00:31:01,095
Dementia in the elderly...

525
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:04,575
is a decline
in higher brain functions.

526
00:31:04,600 --> 00:31:08,935
See if they have problems
with their daily routines,

527
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:13,920
problems with concentration,
thinking, or decision-making,

528
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:18,646
if their planning seems off
or different from usual,

529
00:31:18,671 --> 00:31:23,467
maybe, mixing up names of objects,

530
00:31:23,492 --> 00:31:25,490
or exhibiting
inappropriate behavior,

531
00:31:25,515 --> 00:31:27,440
then you should
take her to see a doctor.

532
00:31:28,560 --> 00:31:31,615
Okay. If I see that...

533
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:35,415
she has these symptoms,
I must take her to the doctor.

534
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:37,415
So she can get well soon.

535
00:31:37,440 --> 00:31:42,208
Oh, but dementia cannot be cured.

536
00:31:42,208 --> 00:31:44,240
We can only slow down the symptoms.

537
00:31:50,675 --> 00:31:51,675
Uncle Ohn.

538
00:31:53,271 --> 00:31:54,440
Okay, just a sec.

539
00:31:54,995 --> 00:31:57,427
Nidnoi, I have to go now.

540
00:31:57,452 --> 00:31:59,028
Thanks for the information.

541
00:31:59,053 --> 00:32:00,927
Sure. Call me if anything comes up.

542
00:32:12,337 --> 00:32:14,160
Ikkyu has been
in the bathroom for a while.

543
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:17,960
Are you going to rinse your hair?

544
00:32:17,985 --> 00:32:19,560
You just left it on for a bit.

545
00:32:19,585 --> 00:32:23,138
This recipe says only five minutes.

546
00:32:23,163 --> 00:32:24,498
Really?

547
00:32:24,889 --> 00:32:27,314
What happens
if you leave it on too long?

548
00:32:27,339 --> 00:32:28,360
Probably nothing.

549
00:32:32,080 --> 00:32:35,553
Are you annoyed with me?
I'm just taking care of my hair.

550
00:32:35,578 --> 00:32:36,578
No.

551
00:32:37,265 --> 00:32:41,007
I'm just thinking about
what I talked about with Nidnoi.

552
00:32:41,680 --> 00:32:42,840
About dementia.

553
00:32:43,099 --> 00:32:44,119
Hmm.

554
00:32:44,209 --> 00:32:47,895
If later on,
we forget each other...

555
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:50,360
Whatever happens, happens.

556
00:32:50,880 --> 00:32:53,494
What hasn't happened yet,
don't worry about it.

557
00:32:53,519 --> 00:32:58,406
We just do our best to prevent
our brains from deteriorating.

558
00:32:59,031 --> 00:33:00,031
Hmm.

559
00:33:00,633 --> 00:33:02,160
It doesn't deteriorate that easily.

560
00:33:03,160 --> 00:33:06,010
But I haven't been sleeping enough.

561
00:33:06,035 --> 00:33:07,824
So sleep enough then.

562
00:33:07,848 --> 00:33:09,257
Starting today.

563
00:33:09,281 --> 00:33:10,296
Now.

564
00:33:10,320 --> 00:33:11,320
Go to sleep.

565
00:33:12,263 --> 00:33:13,336
Very good.

566
00:33:13,361 --> 00:33:16,600
So your face will be bright
and fresh for the camera.

567
00:33:19,280 --> 00:33:20,784
Filming tomorrow.

568
00:33:20,808 --> 00:33:22,028
I'm so excited.

569
00:33:22,053 --> 00:33:23,080
Are the actors ready?

570
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:24,421
- Ready!
- Ready!

571
00:33:24,446 --> 00:33:25,846
But now, let me go rinse my hair.

572
00:33:27,418 --> 00:33:28,418
Ouu...

573
00:33:31,399 --> 00:33:33,766
Raise your hands and inhale.

574
00:33:34,106 --> 00:33:35,763
Lower your hands and exhale.

575
00:33:40,260 --> 00:33:43,343
Hey, little boy! Come here!

576
00:33:43,368 --> 00:33:47,160
Don't call her "little boy"!
She has chosen her path.

577
00:33:47,451 --> 00:33:49,865
If not "little boy,"
what should I use?

578
00:33:49,890 --> 00:33:51,225
"Little girl"?

579
00:33:51,250 --> 00:33:52,943
So difficult.
I won't say anything anymore.

580
00:33:54,640 --> 00:33:56,680
I'm neither "little girl"
nor "little boy."

581
00:33:57,479 --> 00:34:00,673
I am me. Please call me Ikkyu.

582
00:34:00,698 --> 00:34:02,080
Grandpa Ood, Grandma Jib.

583
00:34:03,514 --> 00:34:06,360
- Hello, Ikkyu.
- Hello, Ikkyu.

584
00:34:06,788 --> 00:34:10,481
Meeting this early,
have you eaten yet, dear?

585
00:34:11,168 --> 00:34:12,431
I have.

586
00:34:12,455 --> 00:34:14,463
I even fried eggs myself.

587
00:34:14,488 --> 00:34:16,743
Hmm... Good job.

588
00:34:17,524 --> 00:34:19,399
Have you two eaten yet?

589
00:34:19,424 --> 00:34:22,908
- Oh, yes. Don't worry.
- Don't worry at all.

590
00:34:22,908 --> 00:34:25,642
By the way, are we starting soon?

591
00:34:26,239 --> 00:34:28,456
I'm itching to perform.

592
00:34:28,481 --> 00:34:30,840
I used to be a Likay hero.

593
00:34:32,028 --> 00:34:33,541
My little braggin rights.

594
00:34:34,600 --> 00:34:37,720
Please wait a moment.
The cast isn't all here yet.

595
00:34:38,847 --> 00:34:40,640
Isn't that them?

596
00:34:41,461 --> 00:34:42,461
There, over there.

597
00:34:50,146 --> 00:34:51,800
This way, Uncle Jee, Uncle Ohn!

598
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:00,920
Oh, there...

599
00:35:03,725 --> 00:35:05,280
Hello, Mae Champi.

600
00:35:05,872 --> 00:35:08,348
God bless, dear.

601
00:35:08,373 --> 00:35:12,560
Thank you so much
for helping Ikkyu out.

602
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:14,440
It's better than
staying home alone.

603
00:35:16,196 --> 00:35:19,126
Where's the director?

604
00:35:19,520 --> 00:35:21,680
Over there. Shooting.

605
00:35:21,996 --> 00:35:22,996
Oh.

606
00:35:23,285 --> 00:35:26,280
Are we doing Tai Chi?

607
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:28,000
I can't do that.

608
00:35:32,600 --> 00:35:35,160
No, Ikkyu is making a short film

609
00:35:35,184 --> 00:35:38,423
about what kind of old person
you want to be when you grow up.

610
00:35:38,925 --> 00:35:42,280
So he wants actors
who are a bit older

611
00:35:42,515 --> 00:35:45,120
to portray the diverse future.

612
00:35:45,728 --> 00:35:48,888
All kinds of happy old people.

613
00:35:50,200 --> 00:35:51,526
What?

614
00:35:51,550 --> 00:35:52,763
Only a little over 50.

615
00:35:52,787 --> 00:35:54,496
That's not old.

616
00:35:54,520 --> 00:35:55,560
I think it is.

617
00:35:55,933 --> 00:35:59,046
Do you know
why I was late this morning?

618
00:35:59,071 --> 00:36:01,960
I couldn't find my glasses.
And I forget them every day too.

619
00:36:03,447 --> 00:36:05,534
If you want to be old,
be old by yourself.

620
00:36:05,559 --> 00:36:07,728
As for me,
I'm still alive and kicking.

621
00:36:07,753 --> 00:36:10,517
Yeah, right.

622
00:36:10,542 --> 00:36:13,440
For you, it's called
kicking the bucket soon.

623
00:36:14,183 --> 00:36:15,409
- Hey!
- True.

624
00:36:15,434 --> 00:36:17,707
- Finished your bucket list?
- Watch your mouth!

625
00:36:18,600 --> 00:36:20,360
You two, stop arguing.

626
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:24,360
Today, we are all old people.

627
00:36:27,255 --> 00:36:29,055
Wow...

628
00:36:29,341 --> 00:36:30,511
Next level.

629
00:36:30,536 --> 00:36:33,364
You're really
investing in this role.

630
00:36:33,388 --> 00:36:34,440
Jee is being sarcastic.

631
00:36:36,145 --> 00:36:37,960
- Oh.
- Here.

632
00:36:44,763 --> 00:36:48,224
- Bring it on.
- You're going to lose.

633
00:36:51,565 --> 00:36:54,560
Jira doesn't look very happy.

634
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:57,560
He's probably worried
about the bald wig.

635
00:36:58,278 --> 00:37:00,104
He is losing a lot of hair lately.

636
00:37:00,129 --> 00:37:01,809
Oh... Listen.

637
00:37:02,158 --> 00:37:05,815
Absolutely do not
buy the medicine yourself.

638
00:37:05,840 --> 00:37:07,520
I used to lose hair too.

639
00:37:07,920 --> 00:37:10,330
Whatever anyone said was good,
I bought and took it all.

640
00:37:10,355 --> 00:37:11,560
My hair fell off even more!

641
00:37:11,584 --> 00:37:12,855
- Oh!
- Oh my!

642
00:37:12,880 --> 00:37:15,703
It's completely normal, dear.

643
00:37:16,074 --> 00:37:19,760
Back in the day,
I used to be very beautiful.

644
00:37:21,720 --> 00:37:23,520
But as time passed...

645
00:37:23,520 --> 00:37:26,120
things that used to
be firm started to sag.

646
00:37:27,272 --> 00:37:29,546
But there's one thing
I didn't want to be hard,

647
00:37:29,570 --> 00:37:31,783
that ended up being so hard.

648
00:37:32,334 --> 00:37:34,135
What is it?

649
00:37:34,159 --> 00:37:36,443
What has gotten so hard?

650
00:37:36,468 --> 00:37:38,360
Well...

651
00:37:43,080 --> 00:37:44,144
Don't tell me...

652
00:37:44,169 --> 00:37:45,480
My hearing... you silly!

653
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:49,240
- Hearing.
- Hearing.

654
00:37:50,048 --> 00:37:51,840
Hard of hearing!

655
00:37:56,053 --> 00:37:57,686
- Move here.
- Hmm.

656
00:37:58,280 --> 00:37:59,280
Oh.

657
00:38:00,467 --> 00:38:01,500
Ugh...

658
00:38:02,061 --> 00:38:04,920
Jee, what's wrong? It's your turn.

659
00:38:04,944 --> 00:38:06,480
Oh, right, right.

660
00:38:08,137 --> 00:38:09,880
Here.

661
00:38:11,330 --> 00:38:12,615
- Ouch!
- Right here!

662
00:38:13,510 --> 00:38:14,560
Cut!

663
00:38:17,211 --> 00:38:18,400
Excuse me, Uncle Jee.

664
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:19,400
Yes.

665
00:38:22,922 --> 00:38:24,000
Done.

666
00:38:24,880 --> 00:38:26,720
Ikkyu, I wonder...

667
00:38:27,684 --> 00:38:28,840
Can I not be bald?

668
00:38:28,865 --> 00:38:30,800
It doesn't look very good.

669
00:38:31,520 --> 00:38:35,497
Really? But I think
you are a very handsome bald man.

670
00:38:36,098 --> 00:38:38,952
If you don't believe me,
try putting the wig on Uncle Ohn.

671
00:38:39,770 --> 00:38:41,720
Hey! What do you mean by that?

672
00:38:43,418 --> 00:38:45,360
Whose side are you on?

673
00:38:47,080 --> 00:38:49,560
Come on! Give me the wig.

674
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:51,520
- Okay.
- Let's see.

675
00:38:56,779 --> 00:38:57,779
How is it?

676
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:06,989
Why are you laughing so hard?

677
00:39:08,243 --> 00:39:10,720
Oh!

678
00:39:10,720 --> 00:39:12,800
No way.

679
00:39:13,121 --> 00:39:15,800
We should let Uncle Jee wear it.

680
00:39:15,938 --> 00:39:17,880
My...

681
00:39:18,016 --> 00:39:20,864
Fine! I'll wear it.

682
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:28,556
Everyone ready?

683
00:39:28,880 --> 00:39:30,000
- Ready!
- Ready!

684
00:39:31,240 --> 00:39:32,240
Action!

685
00:39:34,120 --> 00:39:38,416
One... Two... Three, go!

686
00:39:38,441 --> 00:39:42,080
Keep your arms straight!

687
00:39:42,105 --> 00:39:43,840
Arms straight, everyone!

688
00:39:47,115 --> 00:39:48,880
Come on, lift them high!

689
00:40:24,686 --> 00:40:29,183
I want to thank everyone
for helping me out.

690
00:40:29,208 --> 00:40:32,478
You're welcome.
We also want to thank Ikkyu

691
00:40:32,503 --> 00:40:34,950
for inviting old folks
to do something fun.

692
00:40:35,486 --> 00:40:39,840
Yes. You made me
become a star in my old age.

693
00:40:41,446 --> 00:40:43,500
If this old man is no good,
just cut his scene out.

694
00:40:43,525 --> 00:40:45,232
No need to be polite.

695
00:40:46,560 --> 00:40:48,800
Everyone acted like pros.

696
00:40:48,825 --> 00:40:50,704
Hmm...

697
00:40:50,729 --> 00:40:53,280
Once I finish editing,
I'll show you right away.

698
00:40:53,280 --> 00:40:55,059
- Hmm.
- Good, good.

699
00:40:55,084 --> 00:40:58,607
Thank you everyone
for helping him out.

700
00:40:59,128 --> 00:41:03,760
I'll make sure he edits it nicely.

701
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:05,160
It will turn out the best.

702
00:41:06,759 --> 00:41:08,999
Let's go back and edit it.

703
00:41:09,047 --> 00:41:10,143
Let's go.

704
00:41:10,601 --> 00:41:13,640
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

705
00:41:13,665 --> 00:41:15,492
- See you later, Aom and Ikkyu.
- See ya.

706
00:41:15,517 --> 00:41:16,920
- Bye bye.
- Bye...

707
00:41:21,960 --> 00:41:25,600
Jira, Ohn, I've got an idea.

708
00:41:35,658 --> 00:41:38,418
The cause of
hair loss in men is genetic.

709
00:41:40,065 --> 00:41:42,510
My father isn't bald, though.

710
00:41:42,545 --> 00:41:45,045
There can be many other causes.

711
00:41:45,070 --> 00:41:48,080
It could be due to Testosterone

712
00:41:48,113 --> 00:41:51,273
converting into
Dihydrotestosterone.

713
00:41:52,675 --> 00:41:55,321
Why do hormones change
back and forth like that?

714
00:41:55,346 --> 00:41:57,260
It's because we get older.

715
00:41:57,285 --> 00:41:58,480
Oh.

716
00:41:58,505 --> 00:42:01,351
So there's no cure?

717
00:42:01,376 --> 00:42:02,561
There is.

718
00:42:02,585 --> 00:42:05,167
It depends on
what you're comfortable with.

719
00:42:09,120 --> 00:42:10,200
Will it be one session?

720
00:42:10,720 --> 00:42:11,720
Five sessions?

721
00:42:12,400 --> 00:42:13,760
Or ten sessions?

722
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:17,600
There are many options.

723
00:42:24,887 --> 00:42:26,520
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

724
00:42:29,443 --> 00:42:30,443
Yes.

725
00:42:31,997 --> 00:42:32,997
Let's go.

726
00:42:33,365 --> 00:42:35,520
What did the doctor say?

727
00:42:36,100 --> 00:42:37,100
Well...

728
00:42:38,326 --> 00:42:40,326
he offered several treatments.

729
00:42:41,654 --> 00:42:42,963
But the prices are brutal.

730
00:42:42,987 --> 00:42:44,412
I can't afford it.

731
00:42:44,436 --> 00:42:48,080
Having hair but
nothing to eat isn't okay either.

732
00:42:48,825 --> 00:42:51,240
Is there nothing we can do?

733
00:42:51,800 --> 00:42:54,533
You'll be so worried
you won't be able to sleep.

734
00:42:54,857 --> 00:42:55,857
Hmm...

735
00:42:56,600 --> 00:42:58,640
He did tell me
how to take care of it.

736
00:42:59,998 --> 00:43:02,720
What did he say?

737
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:05,725
I'm scared of thinning hair too.

738
00:43:05,750 --> 00:43:08,610
He said we should eat

739
00:43:08,635 --> 00:43:11,995
nutritious food,
supplement with vitamins

740
00:43:12,020 --> 00:43:14,400
- iron, zinc,
- Hmm.

741
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:16,520
and reduce stress.

742
00:43:17,383 --> 00:43:19,720
Everything you said,
I'm already doing it.

743
00:43:19,720 --> 00:43:21,480
So that means I'm good then?

744
00:43:21,505 --> 00:43:23,890
Then you have to see

745
00:43:23,914 --> 00:43:26,851
if anyone in your family
has thinning hair genetics.

746
00:43:28,899 --> 00:43:31,280
Oh no. I'm probably doomed then.

747
00:43:32,309 --> 00:43:33,309
Genetics?

748
00:43:33,334 --> 00:43:36,600
Let's go get pickled crab!

749
00:43:37,497 --> 00:43:38,497
What happened?

750
00:43:38,826 --> 00:43:40,440
What's wrong?

751
00:43:44,960 --> 00:43:45,960
Job,

752
00:43:46,520 --> 00:43:49,200
I'm definitely going to be bald.

753
00:43:50,280 --> 00:43:52,440
Everyone in my family
has thinning hair and goes bald.

754
00:43:53,320 --> 00:43:56,880
And then, you two
will definitely leave me.

755
00:43:56,880 --> 00:43:59,895
Calm down, A.

756
00:43:59,920 --> 00:44:01,640
You're worrying over nothing.

757
00:44:01,920 --> 00:44:04,175
There are plenty
of talented hairdressers.

758
00:44:04,200 --> 00:44:07,972
They'll definitely find
a hairstyle that suits your face.

759
00:44:07,997 --> 00:44:10,200
A good face is half the battle.

760
00:44:12,120 --> 00:44:13,120
Okay.

761
00:44:13,760 --> 00:44:15,961
In that case, before we eat

762
00:44:15,986 --> 00:44:17,600
shall we go to a beauty clinic?

763
00:44:17,600 --> 00:44:18,653
Okay, let's go.

764
00:44:18,678 --> 00:44:20,160
Let's go!

765
00:44:20,444 --> 00:44:23,120
Please come with us too.

766
00:44:24,829 --> 00:44:25,829
Hmm?

767
00:44:26,446 --> 00:44:28,265
- Let's go!
- Fabulous.

768
00:44:31,864 --> 00:44:32,864
Want to go?

769
00:44:49,703 --> 00:44:51,040
- Old Man.
- Hmm.

770
00:44:51,889 --> 00:44:52,889
Thank you.

771
00:44:54,503 --> 00:44:56,400
Look at me.

772
00:44:59,560 --> 00:45:00,973
I'm frowning.

773
00:45:00,997 --> 00:45:02,495
I'm very angry right now.

774
00:45:02,520 --> 00:45:03,553
- Hmm.
- Angry.

775
00:45:03,578 --> 00:45:05,077
I was saying "really?"

776
00:45:05,102 --> 00:45:07,880
Hmm...

777
00:45:08,532 --> 00:45:10,280
- It's weird, right?
- Yeah.

778
00:45:14,184 --> 00:45:15,184
I think...

779
00:45:16,363 --> 00:45:18,120
I probably can't
exercise for two days.

780
00:45:20,485 --> 00:45:23,480
Now that we've entered
into the world of Botox,

781
00:45:24,400 --> 00:45:25,720
do we have to stay forever?

782
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:27,960
I think...

783
00:45:29,091 --> 00:45:30,280
if it makes us feel good

784
00:45:30,812 --> 00:45:32,492
and it's not dangerous,

785
00:45:33,778 --> 00:45:34,840
let's just do it.

786
00:45:35,228 --> 00:45:37,240
Hmm...

787
00:45:38,095 --> 00:45:39,200
So tight.

788
00:45:42,037 --> 00:45:44,760
Let me take
this call from the editor.

789
00:45:44,785 --> 00:45:45,800
Hmm.

790
00:45:53,143 --> 00:45:54,143
Hello.

791
00:45:55,448 --> 00:45:56,520
What's up, Mindy?

792
00:45:57,640 --> 00:46:00,373
Ohn, about the Duckman pilot.

793
00:46:01,523 --> 00:46:02,640
Uh... yes?

794
00:46:03,483 --> 00:46:06,440
Well, the numbers aren't good.

795
00:46:07,093 --> 00:46:08,096
Oh.

796
00:46:08,207 --> 00:46:09,600
Did no one read it?

797
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:11,160
There were some.

798
00:46:11,185 --> 00:46:12,298
But...

799
00:46:13,181 --> 00:46:15,960
it's not enough
to justify further investment.

800
00:46:19,405 --> 00:46:21,080
Oh, is that so?

801
00:46:22,834 --> 00:46:23,834
Ohn.

802
00:46:24,616 --> 00:46:26,200
Please come up with a new story.

803
00:46:27,293 --> 00:46:29,200
Waiting for new ideas from you.

804
00:46:30,120 --> 00:46:31,240
Okay, Mindy.

805
00:46:54,760 --> 00:46:56,160
Hey, Jee.

806
00:46:56,185 --> 00:46:57,220
Hmm?

807
00:47:00,320 --> 00:47:02,440
Cosplaying or
are you hooked on this look?

808
00:47:03,304 --> 00:47:04,310
What are you doing?

809
00:47:05,426 --> 00:47:07,497
Ikkyu called for help.

810
00:47:09,228 --> 00:47:10,228
Oh.

811
00:47:14,462 --> 00:47:15,462
Hmm.

812
00:47:21,240 --> 00:47:22,840
Eh...

813
00:47:24,308 --> 00:47:25,308
Huh?

814
00:47:28,560 --> 00:47:30,160
What's up, Ikkyu?

815
00:47:31,326 --> 00:47:33,440
Uncle Jee, please help me.

816
00:47:34,280 --> 00:47:35,800
What can I do for you?

817
00:47:41,485 --> 00:47:42,485
Say what?

818
00:47:49,000 --> 00:47:50,000
Mmm-hmm.

819
00:47:50,291 --> 00:47:51,520
Just filming sleeping, right?

820
00:47:51,614 --> 00:47:52,614
Hmm.

821
00:47:52,978 --> 00:47:55,240
Just filming a scene
of dying peacefully in sleep.

822
00:47:55,665 --> 00:47:56,665
Hmm.

823
00:47:56,697 --> 00:48:00,175
Hopefully, sleeping on
a high pillow is okay.

824
00:48:00,200 --> 00:48:04,190
Because we just got Botox,
the doctor said not to lie flat.

825
00:48:04,215 --> 00:48:06,000
- Really?
- Hmm.

826
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:07,120
Hmm.

827
00:48:09,815 --> 00:48:10,815
Hmm.

828
00:48:16,023 --> 00:48:18,520
Here, right in the middle.

829
00:48:18,545 --> 00:48:20,160
Hmm.

830
00:48:20,160 --> 00:48:22,080
Try lying down.

831
00:48:22,473 --> 00:48:24,673
- Hmm...
- Here.

832
00:48:25,300 --> 00:48:26,306
Mmm-hmm.

833
00:48:26,772 --> 00:48:28,120
- Okay?
- Mmm-hmm.

834
00:48:34,761 --> 00:48:36,440
Let me...

835
00:48:40,352 --> 00:48:41,352
Okay.

836
00:48:42,469 --> 00:48:44,440
- Ready?
- Do I look peaceful enough?

837
00:48:48,219 --> 00:48:49,345
You look like Dracula.

838
00:48:49,560 --> 00:48:50,720
Good.

839
00:48:51,480 --> 00:48:54,840
I'll stay young forever and ever.

840
00:48:56,891 --> 00:48:58,401
Okay. Ready?

841
00:48:58,426 --> 00:48:59,909
- Hmm.
- When...

842
00:49:00,385 --> 00:49:02,600
When I say action,
hold your breath.

843
00:49:02,991 --> 00:49:04,080
Mmm-hmm.

844
00:49:04,680 --> 00:49:05,711
Ready?

845
00:49:07,040 --> 00:49:08,040
And...

846
00:49:09,465 --> 00:49:10,465
Action!

847
00:49:48,280 --> 00:49:49,340
Cut, cut, cut!

848
00:49:49,796 --> 00:49:51,665
- Cut!
- Hmm?

849
00:49:52,545 --> 00:49:53,545
What?

850
00:49:54,116 --> 00:49:55,116
What's wrong?

851
00:49:56,647 --> 00:49:57,647
Well...

852
00:49:59,880 --> 00:50:01,560
seeing you lying dead...

853
00:50:02,363 --> 00:50:03,520
it breaks my heart.

854
00:50:26,430 --> 00:50:28,280
If I lie dead right here

855
00:50:29,080 --> 00:50:30,760
with you by my side,

856
00:50:31,939 --> 00:50:33,520
I'd consider myself
the luckiest man.

857
00:50:41,960 --> 00:50:43,360
Let's die of old age in our sleep.

858
00:50:43,960 --> 00:50:46,680
At 80, 90, 100, or 200 years old.

859
00:50:46,680 --> 00:50:48,743
If we live that long,

860
00:50:49,360 --> 00:50:51,133
we probably won't be coherent.

861
00:50:51,157 --> 00:50:52,340
No way.

862
00:50:59,800 --> 00:51:00,880
Jee.

863
00:51:02,481 --> 00:51:04,080
You take good care of yourself,

864
00:51:04,800 --> 00:51:06,320
exercise,

865
00:51:06,783 --> 00:51:08,960
- eat healthy food,
- Hmm.

866
00:51:08,960 --> 00:51:10,215
and get enough sleep.

867
00:51:10,240 --> 00:51:11,240
I think...

868
00:51:11,424 --> 00:51:14,720
You're going to be
a super healthy old man.

869
00:51:15,770 --> 00:51:16,770
But as for me...

870
00:51:18,520 --> 00:51:20,440
No one knows the future.

871
00:51:21,105 --> 00:51:23,879
You might end up
being the one taking care of

872
00:51:24,176 --> 00:51:26,160
this bald old man instead.

873
00:51:27,027 --> 00:51:28,800
Oh, so tight.

874
00:51:29,238 --> 00:51:30,320
It's okay.

875
00:51:31,457 --> 00:51:34,360
- Even if you're old and bald...
- Hmm.

876
00:51:34,551 --> 00:51:35,720
you'll still be handsome.

877
00:51:38,435 --> 00:51:40,320
With this Botox tight face?

878
00:51:42,356 --> 00:51:44,960
I want to laugh out loud,

879
00:51:45,564 --> 00:51:46,663
but my face's too tight.

880
00:51:49,345 --> 00:51:52,011
- I'll be right back.
- Hmm.

881
00:52:03,533 --> 00:52:04,558
What is it?

882
00:52:12,194 --> 00:52:13,520
Happy birthday!

883
00:52:21,480 --> 00:52:22,480
Thank you.

884
00:52:23,296 --> 00:52:24,296
Well?

885
00:52:25,554 --> 00:52:26,720
Aren't you going to open it?

886
00:52:30,113 --> 00:52:31,360
Having you here...

887
00:52:32,136 --> 00:52:33,960
is already the best gift.

888
00:52:37,258 --> 00:52:40,440
I want to scream so loud.

889
00:52:40,440 --> 00:52:42,160
I'm so happy, but...

890
00:52:43,240 --> 00:52:44,654
my face is tight from Botox!

891
00:52:47,466 --> 00:52:49,775
Tight here too.

892
00:52:56,895 --> 00:53:00,200
Love you.

893
00:53:01,052 --> 00:53:03,570
Let's stay together
for a very long time.

894
00:53:03,595 --> 00:53:06,040
- Hmm.
- Hmm.

895
00:53:06,361 --> 00:53:07,480
Tight for a long time.

896
00:53:09,154 --> 00:53:10,154
Lips?

897
00:53:25,223 --> 00:53:28,169
"It's you, Ohn!"

898
00:53:33,960 --> 00:53:36,495
Being unemployed at this age...

899
00:53:36,520 --> 00:53:38,040
must be quite difficult.

900
00:53:39,219 --> 00:53:41,363
I have worked
in a company for so long.

901
00:53:42,200 --> 00:53:44,135
I don't know
how to do anything else.

902
00:53:44,160 --> 00:53:45,868
So you can try new things.

903
00:53:45,892 --> 00:53:47,614
Open up to new experiences.

904
00:53:47,638 --> 00:53:48,680
In your 50s?

905
00:53:49,980 --> 00:53:51,740
Just talking about it
makes me want to cry.

906
00:53:53,800 --> 00:53:57,120
From the look in your eyes
and the weight on your shoulders

907
00:53:57,145 --> 00:53:59,162
I know you're the one
carrying the team.

908
00:53:59,187 --> 00:54:01,600
Only fellow team-carriers like us

909
00:54:01,625 --> 00:54:02,840
